In [126]:
# Compare the results between igraph and graphframes 
# 

memdf = pd.read_csv("./r2p1.member", header=None, delimiter=r"\s+",\
                    skiprows=range(0,5))
memdf.columns = ["NodeID","MemberID"]




""" 
filter trim the read dataframe
"""

#groupby the memberid, then get the size of each member 
memsize = memdf.groupby('MemberID').size()

memthree = memsize[memsize > 2]



logbins = np.double(range(100))/100.0 * 5.5
histmem, xhist = np.histogram(memthree.sort_values(axis=0, ascending=False).values,\
                       bins=np.power(logbins,10))


gfsize = sizedf.counts
gfthree = gfsize[gfsize > 2]
histgf, xhist = np.histogram(gfthree.sort_values(axis=0, ascending=False).values,\
                       bins=np.power(logbins,10))



fig = plt.figure(figsize=(9,9))
plt.title(r'Histogram of the subcomponents at $L_{link} = 2.1 h^{-1}$ Mpc')
plt.xlabel(r'$SIZE_{sub} \geq 3$')
plt.ylabel(r'$NUMBER_{sub}$')
plt.axis([2,1e3,0.8,5e4])
plt.xscale('log')
plt.yscale('log')
plt.plot(xhist[1:],histmem,label='igraph')
plt.scatter(xhist[1:],histgf,s=50,marker='x',c='r',label='spark/graphframes')
plt.text(50, 1000, r'TOTAL of  $NUMBER_{sub} = 11,823$', fontsize=15)
plt.legend()

plt.show()
